---

🧭 CORE USER FLOW (MANDATORY)

1. Select Namespace (dropdown)
2. Select Deployment (filtered dropdown)
3. Select Pod (filtered dropdown)
4. Select Tail Size:
   - 100 / 200 / 500 / 1000 / 5000
5. Click “Load Logs”

---

🧠 DATA FETCHING MODEL (CRITICAL)

🔴 NO LIVE STREAMING ("-f") by default

---

🟢 Initial Load (Snapshot)

oc logs <pod> --tail=<N>

After fetch:

- Render logs
- Assign sequential index numbers (see below)
- Store lastSeenTimestamp

---

🟡 Refresh (Manual)

oc logs <pod> --since-time=<lastSeenTimestamp>

---

🔵 Auto Refresh (OPTIONAL BUT REQUIRED FEATURE)

- Interval: user configurable (2s / 5s / 10s)
- Uses same "since-time" logic
- MUST NOT trigger UI scroll or jump

---

🟣 Merge Behavior (VERY IMPORTANT)

- Append new logs at the END
- Maintain strict chronological order (by timestamp)
- Remove duplicates
- Preserve original log order exactly as received

---

🔢 LOG ORDERING & NUMBERING (NEW REQUIREMENT)

Each log line MUST include:

- A sequential index (monotonic increasing)
- Example:

#10421  2026-04-30T09:12:33Z  INFO  Service started
#10422  2026-04-30T09:12:34Z  ERROR Connection failed

Rules:

- Index persists across refreshes
- New logs continue numbering (no reset)
- Index is based on arrival order in UI

---

📊 UI REQUIREMENTS

🟢 Main Log View

- Stable list (NO auto-scroll)
- No jumping content
